security || Based on the provided patch notes, it appears that this is a Security-Related Patch (SRP). The patch addresses a double free vulnerability in the tun driver, which was reported by syzkaller. The bug is described as a KASAN (Kernel Address Sanitizer) double-free or invalid-free issue in the selinux_tun_dev_free_security function. The patch fixes the issue by properly handling register_netdevice() failures and ensuring that priv_destructor() is called when necessary.

The patch notes also mention that this fix is related to a previous commit that aimed to fix inconsistent teardown and release of private netdev state. This further suggests that the patch is addressing a security vulnerability.
